> In this quick, cozy pasta dish, earthy mushrooms meet garlicky dark meat chicken
> and tender penne in a satisfyingly silky and savory sauce. The key? Crème fraîche:
> Similar to sour cream but thicker and tangier, it gives pasta a rich flavor and
> glossy finish. Sprinkle with scallion greens for a pop of color and zippy flavor,
> then dig right in!

== Pasta ==

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

== Sauce & Shrimp ==

While pasta cooks, open package of chicken* and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add @shrimp{10%ounce}, mushrooms, and scallion whites; season with
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
mushrooms are browned and tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in drained penne, 1⁄4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @veggie stock concentrate{1},
@mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @crème fraîche{2%tbsp},
@butter{2%tbsp}, and a pinch of @sugar{pinch} (1/3 cup reserved pasta cooking water,
4 TBSP butter, and a big pinch of sugar for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until
sauce is smooth and everything is coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired.

> Open package of chopped chicken breast* and drain off any excess liquid or rinse
> shrimp* under cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Swap in chopped chicken
> breast or shrimp for dark meat chicken.

== To Serve ==

Divide pasta between shallow bowls. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.